    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Never published before this edition.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 
                    <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀστυκράτης"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀ</supplied>στυκ<unclear>ρά</unclear><supplied reason="lost">τ</supplied> <gap reason="lost" atLeast="2" atMost="3" unit="character"/></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">δαμος</seg></name></persName> Ι<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 
                    <lb n="2a"/><space quantity="2.2" unit="cm"/>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Astykratès <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>damos I<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Astykrates <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>damos I<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Astykrates <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>damos I<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p/>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>Although the fragment is very small, a date may be proposed because the lettering is quite similar to <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr062810</ref>. Line 1 keeps a name without the ending that might 
             help to know at which case it was. At line 2, the compound name in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-δαμος</foreign> was probably followed by his father's name beginning with iota. This leaves many possiblities open,
                 such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἰάσων</foreign>, a name including <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἵππος</foreign> or even a Libyan name such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ιγισαν</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ιαλ</foreign>. One such pair occurs at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr033100</ref>, but its date is very different and 
             we should leave the question open.</p>
             <p>The inventory number corresponds to the reorganisation of the storeroom for inscriptions in the ancient museum, care of Goodchild after World War II. It was thus probably a find of the Italian period.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
